sql_statement.static: SELECT sgr.ConnectionName AS 'Connection Name',  raws.GoodputTxBytes/1e6 AS 'Successful Server Tx Bytes (MB)', rawc.GoodputRxBytes/1e6 AS 'Successful Client Rx Bytes (MB)', (100.0*raws.GoodputTxBytes-100.0*rawc.GoodputRxBytes)/(1.0*raws.GoodputTxBytes) AS 'Throughput Loss Ratio (%)',

AS 'Throughput Loss Threshold (%)' FROM RFC6349ServerGenResults AS sgr JOIN RawTcpServerResults AS raws ON raws.handle = sgr.ServerResultsHandle JOIN RFC6349ClientAnResults AS car ON car.ConnectionIndex = sgr.ConnectionIndex JOIN RawTcpClientResults AS rawc ON rawc.handle = car.ClientResultsHandle

create_report_table.display_name: TCP Throughput Test Results Traffic Check

table_verdict.passed_verdict_explanation: All clients received the necessary bytes sent by their servers.
table_verdict.failed_verdict_explanation: One or more clients received an inadequate number of bytes sent by their servers.

SELECT `Percent of Max-RWND`, `Max TCP Window Size (Bytes)`, `Connection Name`, `Line Rate (Mbps)`, `Ideal TCP Throughput (Mbps)`, `Actual TCP Throughput (Mbps)`, `Ideal TCP Transmitted Bytes (MB)`, `Actual TCP Transmitted Bytes (MB)`, `Retransmitted Bytes (MB)`, `TCP Efficiency (%)` FROM RFC6349TputResultsRawTable
